This made another thought pop into my head (scary I know).  It almost seems like this promotes segregation.  Here in the US some people decide to send their kids to a private religious school, but at least our public schools can house children of all religious backgrounds.  I know that there is a large Muslim population in Europe in general (not sure about the specifics in the UK), and it seems like the current system would push entire groups of people into their own schools, much like what used to happen in the southeastern US.  I think the US has the potential to do that if we don't keep SOCAS in check.  If our schools become more Christian, then Muslims will be in their own schools, Jews in their own schools, etc.  School vouchers would help enable this to happen as well.  I believe that a major reason racism isn't as prominent in our society is because kids can say &quot;hey, black people aren't so bad, I knew this guy at school...&quot;.  Familiarity helps to produce tolerance, and when people are being segregated like that, then people who are different will seem foreign to the average citizen.  A Muslim will go from the guy you sit next to in school to the nameless and faceless statistic in that building across town.  Okay, I'll quit releasing these brain farts now.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
