When a child reaches the age of 18 (or is it 16) and are allowed to choose for themselves whether to stay in the religion or not - is it really made an option to leave?  I remember when we were younger, my brothers best friend was JW...when he reached that age, he decided that he didn't want to be JW anymore...his parents were not happy, and said that they would never buy him anything ever again (despite the fact that they didn't do birthdays, this family bought gifts for their children all year round)...he ummed and ahhhed about it for a while, and decided that he would be JW after all....the very next day he woke up and found an electric guitar at the end of his bed!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
