You can leave but depending on your status as a member you will probably lose your family and friends. JW's are technically not supposed to speak to non-members unless they have to in their day-to-day lives. If you go to a different religion you will probably not have any family or friends that will speak to you. It comes to your own discretion with your family but the majority of JW I know will not speak to the family members that decided to go to a different religion. My whole family doesn’t speak to my dad because he left the JW and went to LDS.<br>
